  m_Name: Readme
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: com.fuzzphyte.utility.editor::FuzzPhyte.Utility.Editor.FPReadmeAsset
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: b521bf5d6ffa177458e7c14188bbf89d, type: 3}
  title: FuzzPhyte Utility
  subtitle: 'Utility Package Documentation '
  version: 1.0.0
  overview: "FP_Utility is designed and built to be a simple set of base classes
    to be used in almost all future FuzzPhyte packages. \nThere is an element of
    Scriptable Object and an element of just simple input/output functions as well
    as some core scripts timed to timers etc. \nThere are a lot of static functions
    to help with file management and Unity Editor management. Please read the full
    readme located on the GitHub if you want more details. This readme file is designed
    to get you into the menu system quickly and understanding at a high level what
    are the core tools that this package manages."
  overviewLinks:
  - label: GitHub Readme
    url: https://github.com/JShull/FP_Utility/blob/main/README.md
  - label: Changelog
    url: https://github.com/JShull/FP_Utility/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md
  sections:
  - heading: FP Header
    showSeparatorBefore: 0
    body: 'FP Header is an editor-only hierarchy organization tool for Unity scenes.
      It lets you create disabled, all-caps GameObjects that act like visual section
      headers in the standard Unity Hierarchy without forcing the grouped objects
      into a parent-child transform relationship. This is useful when you want the
      readability and collapse behavior of folders, but you do not want to change
      transform inheritance or scene structure.



      A header is treated as valid
      when the GameObject name is all caps, the object is inactive, and it has no
      children. Objects that appear after that header in the same sibling scope are
      treated as part of the section until the next valid header is found.


      [FuzzPhyte/Header/Header
      Options](menu:FuzzPhyte/Header/Header Options) .'
    links: []
  - heading: Scene Asset Tool
    showSeparatorBefore: 1
    body: 'FP Scene Asset Tool is an editor window that scans the active scene and
      builds a reference list of the external assets used by that scene. It is intended
      to help you audit scene dependencies such as materials, meshes, textures, audio
      clips, prefab assets, animation assets, ScriptableObjects, fonts, and other
      referenced content so you can spot misplaced project references, redundant
      assets, or content coming from the wrong part of the project.



      The
      tool deduplicates assets by path, groups them by detected type, tracks which
      scene GameObjects reference each asset, and marks package or built-in dependencies
      as non-selectable so you can focus on project content you actually control.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Scene](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Scene/Asset
      Tool).'
    links: []
  - heading: Action Event Scanner
    showSeparatorBefore: 0
    body: 'To help identify and locate various actions/events that any FuzzPhyte
      package might be using. Really an editor tool for myself but realized it might
      come in handy for others.


      FP Action-Event Scanner is an editor-only
      package audit window for finding C# `event`, `delegate`, and `Action` declarations
      or usages across FuzzPhyte package folders. It is intended as an internal package-maintenance
      tool when you need a quick map of where event-style communication is happening
      across `FP_` packages.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Editor/Action-Event Scanner](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Editor/Action-Event
      Scanner)'
    links: []
  - heading: Audio Combine
    showSeparatorBefore: 1
    body: 'FP Audio Combine Tool is an editor-only multi-clip audio assembly window.
      It is intended for building a combined WAV from several AudioClips while preserving
      per-clip trimming, spacing, ordering, gain, and inclusion settings.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Audio](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Audio/Combine
      Tool).'
    links: []
  - heading: Audio Segment
    showSeparatorBefore: 0
    body: 'FP Audio Segment Tool is an editor-only AudioClip trimming and cleanup
      helper. It lets you preview a source clip waveform, choose an in/out segment,
      add independent mute or cut regions, and export the processed result as a WAV
      asset. Not as elaborate as the Audio Combine tool but easy to split a file
      in a pinch.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Audio/Segment](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Audio/Segment
      Tool).'
    links: []
  - heading: Mesh Tools
    showSeparatorBefore: 1
    body: 'There are a few variations of Mesh Tools. You can slice an existing mesh,
      you can combine some existing meshes, you can generate convex hull solutions
      for others (think LOD), you can extrude from an SVG (entire SVG selection editor
      window) and you can generate a mesh based on a grid and all sorts of other
      parameters associated with mesh generation. Please see the package readme for
      details on these tools as they are elaborate.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Slicer](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Mesh
      Slicer)

      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Combine](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Combine
      Meshes)

      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Convex](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Convex
      Generator)

      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/SVG Extruder](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/SVG
      Extruder)

      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Mesh Generator](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Mesh/Mesh
      Generator)'
    links: []
  - heading: 360 Video Mesh Generation
    showSeparatorBefore: 0
    body: 'Quick tool to generate spheres, ellipses, or quads for use in 360 video
      work.


      [FuzzPhyte/Utility/Video/360 Sphere](menu:FuzzPhyte/Utility/Video/FP
      Video Sphere Generator)'
    links:
    - label: GitHub Readme
      url: https://github.com/JShull/FP_Utility/blob/main/README.md
